commit.message: Look for the correct value when returning `undefined`
Generate documentation for hex.pm from README.md and EDoc
For debugging hex, use DEBUG instead of crashdump

Update meck dependency used for running tests

But keep using the old proper v1.3, as the new v1.4 doesn't
support Erlang 19.3, which ejabberd still supports.
https://github.com/proper-testing/proper/commit/e249f584ad989ed37974acc32c9647a54fd92dbd

Implicit Grant doesn't  need client secret

As RFC mentions:

> The implicit grant type does not include client authentication, and
   relies on the presence of the resource owner and the registration of
   the redirection URI.

Client secret is not needed.
Add support to send C coverage. Don't cache. Move hex plugin to Action
Dirty workaround: run tests with rebar2 before rebar3
Switch from Travis to Github Actions
